  "program_name": "Beginner Full Body Recomp Program",
  "overview": "This 4-week program is designed for a beginner aiming for body recomposition. It alternates between strength-focused and hypertrophy-focused weeks with a deload in the fourth week. The program uses a full body split, training three times per week, with light cardio included. Exercises are selected to cover all major muscle groups with a focus on both compound and isolation movements.",
  "progression_rules": "Linear progression: Add 2.5-5 lbs when all reps are completed with good form. RPE and RIR are set to 0 for beginner level.",
